Sokoto State Government has signed contracts worth over N6 billion with various contractors who were also mobilised with 30 per cent of the total amount. The contracts are the construction of the new Government Girls Academy Kasarawa awarded to Calder Construction Company, the new Abdullahi Bara’u Secondary School, Dogon Daji, awarded to Erbi Project Consulting Engineering. The two projects will gulp N2.401 billion and N2.17 billion respectively. A statement signed by the special adviser on media and publicity to the governor, Muhammad Bello, said other projects are the construction of a modern sports arena and an indoor sports hall awarded to Qualitrends Global Solutions at the cost of N1.23 billion and N447 million naira respectively. ALSO READ: COVID-19: Ekiti Attorney General, cabinet members test positive Bello further said the governor, who was represented by the state Attorney-General and Commissioner for Justice, Barrister Suleiman Usman (SAN), charged the contracting firms to ensure that the execution of the projects is according to the contractual agreements. He said the state government is committed to providing all necessary support and cooperation to them in order to make it possible for them to execute quality projects. Barrister Usman called on the client ministries- Ministry of Basic and Secondary Education and Ministry of Youths and Sports Development, to ensure effective supervision of the projects. He appealed to people in the state to cooperate with the contractors in the discharge of their duties. In his remarks, the representative of the contracting firms, Usman Murtala Banye, thanked the government for awarding the contracts to them and promised to execute the projects according to specification. YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE Nigeria’s COVID-19 Cases Hit 40,532 After 555 New Infections Nigeria’s tally of confirmed COVID-19 cases on Saturday rose to 40,532 as 555 new infections were announced by the Nigeria Centre fo